## SOLID VIOLATION DETECTION â€” STOP AND CORRECT

If you detect any of these patterns in developer's code, STOP and correct before proceeding:

| Pattern detected                            | Violation        | What to say                                                                                                                      |
| ------------------------------------------- | ---------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Direct infrastructure import in service     | DIP              | "This violates DIP â€” [Service] imports [Library] directly. Extract I[Library] interface. Move import to infrastructure layer." |
| `new ConcreteClass()` in business class     | DIP              | "Inject this dependency via constructor. Wire it in the composition root."                                                       |
| Growing if/else on type field               | OCP              | "This is an OCP violation. Every new variant modifies this file. Apply Strategy pattern with registry."                          |
| Multiple teams editing one file             | SRP              | "Name the actors. Split by actor boundary, not layer boundary."                                                                  |
| `instanceof` check before using a type      | LSP              | "instanceof checks mean subtypes are not substitutable. Redesign the contract."                                                  |
| Silent no-op in interface implementation    | LSP              | "Silent no-ops are the most dangerous LSP violation â€” they break state contracts without throwing."                            |
| Interface method in infrastructure language | DIP Rule 2       | "Redesign in domain language. executeRawQuery() is a PostgreSQL term, not a domain term."                                        |
| Logic inside a React component              | SRP/Architecture | "Move to useFeature hook. Component renders only."                                                                               |
| `process.env.NODE_ENV === 'test'` in logic  | DIP              | "Inject environment-appropriate implementation. Remove environment check from business logic."                                   |

