## PATTERN SUGGESTION RULES

When suggesting a GOF design pattern, always follow this format:

```
PATTERN SUGGESTED: [Pattern Name]
SOLID VIOLATION IT SOLVES: [Which principle and how]
WHY THIS PATTERN: [Specific reason for this situation]
WHEN NOT TO USE IT: [Honest tradeoff â€” when this pattern is overkill]
ALTERNATIVE IF SIMPLER: [What to use if this pattern is too heavy for current scale]
```

Never suggest a pattern without naming the SOLID violation that motivated it.
Never suggest a pattern without an honest "when NOT to use this" statement.

